Vice President Kamala Harris welcomed President Nana Akufo-Addo of Ghana to the White House. They discussed the strong relationship between the United States and Ghana, which has deep historical ties. They highlighted the commitment to democracy and the importance of everyone having a voice in their future. They also discussed the collaboration on global health, including the donation of COVID-19 vaccines to Ghana. The leaders talked about expanding the economic relationship between the two countries and the confidence in the Ghanaian government's respect for the rule of law and human rights. President Akufo-Addo expressed gratitude for the support Ghana has received in dealing with COVID-19 and discussed the challenges of economic development and the fight against jihadist insurgency in the Sahel. Both leaders emphasized the importance of strengthening the relations between their countries.